
[1]bishopric

   BISH'OPRIC,n. [bishop and ric, jurisdiction.]

   1. A diocese; the district over which the jurisdiction of bishop
   extends. in England, are twenty-four bishoprics, besides that of Sodor
   and Man; in Ireland, eighteen.

   2. The charge of instructing and governing in spiritual concerns;
   office. Acts.1.20.
